## Cloning a private GitHub repo

The machine's git credential helper doesn't work reliably. Use the token-in-URL method:

```bash
TOKEN=$(gh auth token)
git clone "https://${TOKEN}@github.com/OWNER/REPO.git" /path/to/destination
```

Then immediately set your identity:

```bash
cd /path/to/destination
git-id
```

