## Installing a project with a private GitHub dependency

If any dependency is hosted on a private GitHub repo, add a URL override once per dependency owner using your **PAT**:

```bash
PAT=your_personal_access_token_here
git config --global url."https://${PAT}@github.com/OWNER/".insteadOf "https://github.com/OWNER/"
```

**If `uv sync` / `npm install` breaks again with "Repository not found":** your PAT expired or was revoked. Generate a new one, then re-run:

```bash
# Remove old entry first
git config --global --unset url."https://OLD_PAT@github.com/OWNER/".insteadOf
# Add new entry
PAT=your_new_pat_here
git config --global url."https://${PAT}@github.com/OWNER/".insteadOf "https://github.com/OWNER/"
```

Remove this section if the project has no private GitHub dependencies.

